				 CPM lips sealed on Taslima
 OUR BUREAU																								Calcutta, Nov. 29: The CPM, breathing easy after the Centre decided to provide shelter to Taslima Nasreen in Delhi, today refused to break its silence on the Bangladeshi writers wish to return to Calcutta. 																								We did not discuss Taslima, CPM spokesperson Shyamal Chakraborty said after a state secretariat meeting. Chakraborty had earlier said that the secretariat would decide its stand on Taslima today. 																								At Writers Buildings, state chief secretary Amit Kiran Deb hedged queries about the governments position. Its a very sensitive issue. Whatever the position, the chief minister will tell you, he said. 																								Pranab pill 																								Pranab Mukherjee today listed three donts for Taslima  do not indulge in politics, do not create problems in Indias diplomatic ties with any country and do not hurt peoples sentiments.																								Islam is a religion that preaches universal love and brotherhood. Objections are reasonable if anybody tries to malign it, the foreign minister said.
